        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Isolated neonatal sclerosing cholangitis is a rare genetic biliary tract disease characterized by severe neonatal-onset cholangiopathy with patent bile ducts and absence of ichthyosiform skin lesions. Patients present with jaundice acholic stools hepatosplenomegaly and high serum gamma-glutamyltransferase activity. Liver histology shows portal fibrosis ductular proliferation hepatocellular metallothionein deposits and intralobular bile-pigment accumulations. Some patients may also have renal disease."
        },
